  "prompt": "Why don't people answer me on Quora?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why people may not be responding to your questions on Quora:\n\n1. **Interest Level**: The topic may not be engaging or relevant to many users, leading to fewer responses.\n\n2. **Clarity of the Question**: If your question is unclear or vague, people might not know how to answer it or what specifically you are looking for.\n\n3. **Technical Complexity**: If your question requires specialized knowledge, it may only attract responses from a limited audience, potentially reducing the number of answers.\n\n4. **Timing**: Depending on when you post your question, it may not reach users when they are most active on the platform.\n\n5. **Engagement**: If you haven't engaged with the community (e.g., answering questions or providing feedback), others may be less inclined to respond to you.\n\n6. **Profile Visibility**: Sometimes, if your profile is new or lacks credibility, users may be hesitant to engage.\n\n7. **Repetition**: If similar questions have been asked multiple times, users might not feel inclined to answer again.\n\nTo increase the likelihood of receiving answers, consider refining your questions, engaging with other users, and sharing relevant content on the platform!",
